SIMPLE: hypernym
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hypernym
<hw>hypernym</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a word that is more generic or more
abstract than a given word; a word designating a class of which the
given word is a member. Inverse of <inv>subtype</inv> and
<inv>hyponym</inv>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> superordinate, superordinate word.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

